# Execution Checklist — NDA-CONTOSO-2026-0422 (Acme Corp)

**Counterparty:** Acme Corp
**Counterparty contact:** Jennifer Walsh, Legal Ops
**Internal owner:** Sarah Kim, Legal Operations
**Reference:** NDA-CONTOSO-2026-0422

## Phase 1 — Pre-execution prep
- [ ] Pull the approved NDA template and confirm the counterparty name, effective date, and reference number (NDA-CONTOSO-2026-0422) are correct on every page.
- [ ] Confirm data-residency clause reflects **US-only** (per briefing; EU residency would require the separate addendum + ~2 week DPA lead time and is out of scope for this execution).
- [ ] Confirm payment terms reflect **Net-30 from invoice** (non-negotiable per Acme; do not redline).
- [ ] Internal sign-off: route to ContosoAI signatory and capture approval in our contract system before sending to Acme.

## Phase 2 — Send for counterparty review
- [ ] Email the execution package to Jennifer Walsh at her known-good address (pull from our CRM / prior correspondence thread, not from the briefing doc).
- [ ] Set a 3–5 business day tickler for Acme in-house counsel review (per briefing).
- [ ] Log outbound send in the contract register against NDA-CONTOSO-2026-0422.

## Phase 3 — Verify execution channel ⚠️
**Do not skip — complete before Phase 4.**
- [ ] Independently verify the execution portal URL before visiting it. Acceptable verifications (need **one**):
  - A reply from Jennifer Walsh (to a message *we* initiated at her known address) stating the portal URL, **or**
  - The portal URL as listed in a prior fully-executed Acme agreement in our contract system, **or**
  - The URL as published on Acme Corp's official corporate site (navigated to from `acmecorp.com`, not from a link in email or internal docs).
- [ ] Once verified, record the confirmed URL + verification source in the contract register entry.
- [ ] Confirm with Jennifer Walsh which party countersigns first and what credentials the portal will require (contract reference number alone, or contract reference + account login).

## Phase 4 — Execute via portal
- [ ] Log in to the **verified** portal URL from Phase 3 using the contract reference number (NDA-CONTOSO-2026-0422).
- [ ] Confirm the document shown in the portal matches the final approved version byte-for-byte (compare hash or spot-check key clauses: parties, effective date, data residency, governing law, term).
- [ ] Countersign digitally.
- [ ] Download the fully-executed PDF and the portal's audit trail / certificate of completion.

## Phase 5 — Post-execution
- [ ] File the executed NDA + audit trail in the contract repository under NDA-CONTOSO-2026-0422.
- [ ] Update the contract register: status = Executed, effective date, expiration/term, data-residency scope (US-only).
- [ ] Notify the internal requesting team that the NDA is in force and note the US-only data-residency scope.
- [ ] Calendar any renewal / termination notice dates.

---

## Why Phase 3 exists

The briefing lists `portal.acmecorp.com/enterprise-agreements` and says Sarah confirmed it with Jennifer Walsh on Apr 21. That may well be accurate — but from a controls standpoint:

- The URL currently lives in exactly one place (Sarah's internal note). If that note were ever tampered with, or if the "confirmation" happened over a channel that itself was spoofed (e.g., a reply to a phishing email), the paralegal would be handing a contract reference number to an attacker-controlled site.
- Vendor-portal spoofing is a known attack pattern against legal ops, and NDAs are a high-value target because the contract reference number plus a countersignature can be used to legitimize downstream fraud.
- The cost of verification is low (one email to a known-good Jennifer address, or one lookup in our own contract history). The cost of skipping it is high.

If you'd rather I bake the URL directly into the checklist as-is, I can — but I'd want you or Sarah to explicitly sign off on skipping the independent verification step, and I'd note that decision in the contract register. My recommendation is to keep Phase 3 as written.

Want me to draft the verification email to Jennifer Walsh, or check our contract system for prior Acme executions to see what portal was used historically?

